
File: README.sudo
Description: Give direction related to 'sudo'

If sudo has not been installed:
    login as 'root' user
    apt-get install sudo

Once sudo is installed, it is useful to set/allow user that
sudo privileges to no longer be prompted with password everytime.
To do this:
    a. as a 'root' user, do 'visudo'
    b. or as a user with sudo privilege, do 'sudo visudo'
    c. then add the following line:

%sudo ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL
